hdiutil pmap: display partition map
Usage:	hdiutil pmap [-options <optstr>] <image|device>
	Option string values ["xsSgcvk"]:
	    r raw		- process all without modification
	    x extended		- process all entries 2K & 512 and merge
	    s sectorize		- return all quantities in sectors
	    S sort		- sort all entries by block number
	    g generate free	- account for all space
	    c combine free	- combine adjacent freespace entries
	    f fix final		- final entry will end at end of device!
	    v volume synthesize - no map -> single entry
	    k skip zero-length	- skip zero length entries
	    K skip void/free	- skip all free & void partitions
	    m merge free space	- try to merge small free entries into previous
	    i ignore shims	- ignore small alignment entries (<32 blocks)

	Common options:
	    -encryption <crypto method>
	    -stdinpass
	    -srcimagekey <key>=<value>	(-imagekey is a synonym)
	    -shadow <shadowfile>
	    -insecurehttp
	    -cacert <file|dir>
	    -verbose
	    -debug
	    -quiet
